<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-02-17T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-02-17T23:00:00-05:00" n="23" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d23">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13976: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-02-18T12:00:00+08:00">February 18,
                                        1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 18—10:20
                                    a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>81. My 77, February 15, noon. National Government in a mandate issued
                                February 17 restored to Chang Hsueh Liang his civic rights of <pb facs="0034" n="27" xml:id="pg_27"/> which he had been deprived
                                for 5 years by judgment of high court martial of the Military
                                Affairs Commission on December 31, 1936. Question of restoration of
                                former rank still unsettled.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>